Orthographical error? In GEN 36:23, the BHS Hebrew is עַלְוָ֥ן [alvan].  The Strongs reference for this name points to עַלְוָן [alvan] (with a vav) rather than עַלְיָ֧ן [aliyan] (with a yod).

Orthographical error? In GEN 36:39, the BHS Hebrew is הֲדַ֔ר [hadar].  The Rahlfs' Septuaginta of 1CH 1:50 more closely aligns to Hadad with Αδαδ [Adad].
Orthographical error? In GEN 36:40, the BHS Hebrew is עַֽלְוָ֖ה [alvah] although some minority manuscripts contain עַלְיָה [aliyah].
